## RequestsList Collection [/api/v2/users/requests/]
### List All Request [GET]

Get all requests
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array[Request, Request, Request, Request, Request])


### Make a New Request [POST]
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (Request Post)

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Request)


## Request Collection [/api/v2/users/requests/{request_id}/]
### Get a Request [GET]

An authenticated user can view a single requests
+ Parameters
    + request_id (number) - ID of the Request in the form of an integer

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Request)

### Update Request [PUT]

An authenticated user can update a single requests
+ Parameters
    + request_id (number) - ID of the Request in the form of an integer

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Request)


### Delete Request [DELETE]

An authenticated user can delete a single requests
+ Parameters
    + request_id (number) - ID of the Request in the form of an integer

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Request)

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {"message": "Request not found"}

# Group Admin Endpoints

## Get All requests [/api/v2/requests/]
### Get All [GET]
An Admin can get all the requests inthe application
+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array[Request, Request, Request, Request, Request])

## Approve request [/api/v2/requests/{request_id}/approve/]
### Approve Request [PUT]
An Admin can approve a request
+ Parameters
    + request_id (number) - ID of the Request in the form of an integer

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {"message": "Request has been successfully approved"}


## Resolve request [/api/v2/requests/{request_id}/resolve/]
### Resolve Request [PUT]
An Admin can resolve approved requests in the application
+ Parameters
    + request_id (number) - ID of the Request in the form of an integer

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {"message": "Request has been successfully resolved"}

## Reject request [/api/v2/requests/{request_id}/reject/]
### Reject Request [PUT]
An Admin can reject a request
+ Parameters
    + request_id (number) - ID of the Request in the form of an integer

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {"message": "Request has been successfully rejected"}


